Yet, if you look closer around the basin, you'll find an odd opening in the darkness of it all. Hidden beneath the cover of the snow, a dark cave exists for all sorts of illegal activities. It's quite hard to notice this, but it's there if you look for it. The cavern entrance is only about 4 feet by 7 feet, but it quickly expands outward once you step in. Inside, a small room, similar to a cavern is here. Pillars of stone and worn out rocks lie around the area, but other than that it's mostly empty. It's completely dark inside, so you might need a light of sorts to make your way around. For a cave, it's definitely on the smaller side of things, and makes but an indent into the mountain. The snow doesn't make its way into here, making this one of the few areas without snow. But it's still cold. The cave itself is made of stone. No surprise there. Large and small stone pillars hold it up, and keep it from collapsing in on itself. There are a few leaks weirdly, and some dripping water can be found falling from the ceiling. Interestingly, some large glowing crystals are towards the back, providing some light. Observing them, they really do look like actual rocks. Other than that though, it can be a nice place to stay.
